summary: Email chain between Helen V. Cantwell and an unnamed AUSA regarding scheduling a call to discuss the Epstein matter. The AUSA identifies themselves as part of the prosecution team, and Cantwell is attempting to coordinate a discussion, referencing a prior voicemail about 'Mr. [Epstein]'.

persons.name: Helen V. Cantwell
persons.context: The sender/recipient of emails attempting to schedule a call with a federal prosecutor to discuss the Epstein matter. She mentions being on her way to a meeting at the NYAG.

events.title: Scheduling call about Epstein matter
events.description: Email exchange to coordinate a phone call between Helen V. Cantwell and an AUSA on the Epstein prosecution team to discuss the case.

keyFacts: An unnamed Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) confirms they are 'one of the AUSAs on the Epstein case' and are meeting with their team.
Helen V. Cantwell is seeking to discuss the 'Epstein matter' and references a prior voicemail left about 'Mr. [Epstein]'.
The correspondence indicates active coordination within the prosecution team and with external parties regarding the Epstein case in July 2019.
Cantwell mentions having a meeting at the NYAG (New York Attorney General's office) on the same day.
